      <hedline>
        <hl1>NO CHANGE IN BRAZIL'S RATE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's Central Bank Monetary Policy Committee maintains interest rates at 16.5 percent after unexpected large surge in inflation last month led to fears that government woujld overhoot its year-end inflation target (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's Central Bank Monetary Policy Committee maintained interest rates at 16.5 percent after an unexpectedly large surge in inflation last month led to fears that the government would overshoot its year-end inflation target. Economists say the cautious stance was attributable in part to uncertainty over the future of international oil prices. The committee has reduced interest rates three times since June.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
